WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:03.640 align:middle line:10%
>> The US has already sent
drones to Mars in the form

00:00:03.640 --> 00:00:04.780 align:middle line:10%
of NASA's rovers.

00:00:04.780 --> 00:00:06.730 align:middle line:10%
But now, a California
entrepreneur

00:00:06.730 --> 00:00:10.570 align:middle line:10%
has big ambitions to
send humans to Mars.

00:00:10.570 --> 00:00:13.840 align:middle line:10%
Elon Musk is the billionaire
founder of the SpaceX

00:00:13.840 --> 00:00:15.550 align:middle line:10%
spaceflight company.

00:00:15.550 --> 00:00:17.500 align:middle line:10%
Earlier this month,
he revealed plans

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:20.740 align:middle line:10%
to eventually establish a colony
on the red planet that would

00:00:20.740 --> 00:00:23.140 align:middle line:10%
house up to 80,000 people.

00:00:23.140 --> 00:00:26.740 align:middle line:10%
The $36 billion scheme is still
decades from being realized,

00:00:26.740 --> 00:00:28.690 align:middle line:10%
but Musk's vision
is invigorating

00:00:28.690 --> 00:00:33.200 align:middle line:10%
astronomers and dreamers about
the future of a man in space.

00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:34.000 align:middle line:90%